Fujitsu Says It Will Boost Shipments of Chip Processors for Automobiles

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-05-30T02:50:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/fujitsu-says-it-will-boost-shipments-of-chip-processors-for-automobiles.html
Fujitsu Ltd. (6702)  plans to increase
shipments of microcontrollers used in cars. Fujitsu’s
semiconductor unit will begin sample shipments of
microcontrollers for auto electronic control units today and at
the end of the year, according to a statement on Fujitsu’s
website.  The Japanese electronics maker aims for sales of 25 million
microcontrollers by fiscal 2014, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  